Diagnosis. Pleurota bicostella is a relatively large species (wingspan 20–24 mm ) compared to most congeners. It is characterized by pale grey forewing mixed with white scales and distinct black discal and discocellular spots. In a rare aberration, P. bicostella ab. adscriptella Krulikowski, 1908, the forewing is darker, brownish grey without white irroration (
Tokár et al . 2005
). The moderately broad posterior lobe of juxta compared to related species and the crescent-shaped valval lobe in the male genitalia, and small posterior signa in the female genitalia are diagnostic.

Biology. The larva feeds on the leaves of Calluna and Erica in a silken web (
Tokár et al . 2005
).
